      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model selection must be justified by material characterization data; contact formulation documented and sensitivity-tested.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V screw and PEEK rod modeled as linear elastic with moduli from coupon tensile tests (n=5 per lot). Augmented Lagrange contact with friction coefficient μ=0.3 (from tribology literature) used at screw-rod interface. Sensitivity study over μ=0.2–0.4 showed <3% QoI variation. Model form appropriate for sub-yield loading regime."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
