    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors were formally assessed. Eleven factors met or exceeded required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3; this gap is accepted given the standardized single-condition ASTM F1717 protocol and the corroborating multi-laboratory experimental dataset. The factor 'Relevance of the validation activities to the COU' was not formally scored on the grounds that the validation scope is identical to the COU scope, rendering a separate relevance gradation unnecessary. Overall credibility is judged sufficient to support a Medium assurance level decision for a modelRiskLevel 3 application.",
